About The Hindley Street Country Club (HSCC) is an Australian group which was founded in 2017 by arranger / producer Constantine Delo. The band specializes in performing covers, which have achieved huge success through social media.
They started as a group of Adelaide musicians, recording re-arranged covers and uploading them to Facebook and YouTube weekly. The HSCC has amassed over 540 million YouTube views with over 940,000 subscribers globally and accumulated over a billion views across social media platforms.
Following on from major internet success, they now tour throughout the world &amp; they are still releasing videos weekly on YouTube every Friday.
YouTube (HSCC) They have covered a huge amount of songs, Here are just a few of my favourites;
Easy Lover (Philip Bailey, Phil Collins) Can’t Get Enough Of Your Love (Barry White) End Of The Road (Boys II Men) Le Freak (Chic) Fresh (Kool &amp; The Gang) September (Earth Wind &amp; Fire) P.Y.T. / Pretty Young Thing (Michael Jackson) Isn&rsquo;t She Lovely (Stevie Wonder) Ride Like The Wind (Christopher Cross) - Live YouTube (Sing It Live) There is also another excellent YouTube channel called Sing It Live, which a few of the HSCC band members appear to be involved in, here are some of my favourites;
Only When You Leave (Spandau Ballet) Spinning Around (Kylie Minogue) Get Into the Groove (Madonna) Friday I’m In Love (The Cure) Murder on the Dancefloor (Sophie Ellis-Bextor) I Feel for You (Prince, Chaka Khan) Disco Inferno (The Trammps) About HSCC Here are a few interesting videos about HSCC;
